---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import RandomColor from '../components/RandomColor.astro';
import Button from '../components/Button.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Services — AI Automation Systems for Remote Teams"
  description="AI document processing, multi-source data retrieval agents, and reporting automation for remote-first companies that want to replace manual spreadsheet and data workflows."
>
  <section>
    <h1>
      Services for <RandomColor>AI automation</RandomColor>, document processing, data pipelines, and workflow automation
    </h1>
    <p>
      I help operations managers and founders at 10–50 person remote companies replace fragile spreadsheet workflows with reliable Python systems, AI data pipelines, and automated reporting — without hiring a full-time engineer.
    </p>
    <p style="text-align: center; margin-top: 1rem;">
      Currently available for part-time remote contracts — 10–20 hrs/week
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>1. AI document processing pipelines</h2>
    <p>
      Best for teams manually processing invoices, receipts, PDFs, scanned documents, or inconsistent business records.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>structured extraction from typed and scanned documents</li>
      <li>OCR and LLM fallback for irregular formats</li>
      <li>fixed-schema outputs for downstream systems</li>
      <li>Python and FastAPI backends with validation, logging, and reliable handoff</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>2. Multi-source data retrieval agents</h2>
    <p>
      Best for remote teams whose business data is spread across CRMs, spreadsheets, databases, and SaaS tools.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>connect Google Sheets, APIs, databases, and internal tools</li>
      <li>make business data searchable and queryable in plain English</li>
      <li>build retrieval pipelines with LLMs and vector search where useful</li>
      <li>design secure access, audit logging, and maintainable data flows from day one</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>3. Reporting and workflow automation</h2>
    <p>
      Best for teams spending hours every week consolidating data, assembling reports, or moving information between disconnected systems.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>scheduled Python reporting pipelines</li>
      <li>API integrations and data sync workflows</li>
      <li>alerts when something needs attention</li>
      <li>spreadsheet-to-system upgrades that keep familiar workflows but remove manual effort</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Typical client fit</h2>
    <p>
      I work exclusively with remote-first companies — primarily in the US, UK, Canada, and Australia. My clients are typically operations managers or founders at 10–50 person companies who are scaling past what spreadsheets can handle.
    </p>
    <p>
      If your team is manually consolidating data from multiple tools, spending hours on reporting that should take minutes, or processing documents by hand, I can automate that workflow with reliable, maintainable Python systems.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Engagement style</h2>
    <p>
      I work async-first — detailed written communication, clear documentation, and no need for overlapping timezones. I’m based in India (IST, UTC+5:30) and regularly work with teams in the US, UK, and Australia.
    </p>
    <p>
      Available for part-time retainer engagements and scoped project work. Every system is documented, tested, and handed over with enough context for your team to maintain it.
    </p>
    <p style="text-align: center; margin-top: 1.25rem;">
      <Button href="https://calendly.com/mdhawal94/30min">Book a free 20-min discovery call →</Button>
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
